    <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng">
 	<!--translation encoded as per EG §9.2 -->
	<p>Om. Let there be no obstacle! As follows is the decree of Rahyang Niskala Wastu Kancana<!-- Aditia: we need to choose whether in translating we adapt spelling of names to EYD, or to "loose transliteration" as per TG. In the latter case, we would have here Rahyaṅ Niskala Vasti Kañcana. -->, that came down to Rahyang Ningrat Kancana<!-- Or: "the lord of Rat Kancana"? --> and also to His Highness now at Pakuan Pajajaran.</p> 
	<p>Do not omit to take care of the inhabitants of Jayagiri and the inhabitants of Sundasembawa.</p> 
	<p>If there is someone providing them livelihood, do not be eager to overcrowd/overburden him/them<!-- Adit: we need to chose here. --> with the <foreign>dasa</foreign>, <foreign>calagara</foreign>, <foreign>kapas timbang</foreign>, <foreign>pare dongdang</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation">taxes</supplied>.</p><!-- Aditia: some of the fiscal terms can actually be translated... --> 
	<p>Also with regard to all the <supplied reason="subaudible">people at the</supplied> mouth of the river: do not be eager to ask them toll. Because those who are loved, as it were, <supplied reason="subaudible">themselves</supplied> love the world, <supplied reason="subaudible">and are those</supplied> who firmly put into practice the divine ordinances.</p> 
         </div>
