           <p>The plates from Kebantenan were first edited by Holle (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:Holle1867_01"/><citedRange>559-567</citedRange>, <ptr target="bib:Holle1872_01"/><citedRange>367-369</citedRange></bibl>); they were re-edited by Pleyte who provided some facsimiles of the plates (<bibl><ptr target="bib:Pleyte1911_01"/><citedRange>163-167</citedRange>; and <citedRange>198-199</citedRange></bibl>); and edited again by Boechari (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:Boechari1985-1986_01"/><citedRange>103-107</citedRange><!-- Aditia: when encoding inscrioptions edited by Boechari, please also indicate with <citedRange unit="item"> the E. number in question; see e.g. my file Maribong.xml; here, since we are citing all Kebantenan inscriptions as a block, we could say <citedRange unit="item">E.42-E.45</citedRange  --></bibl>), who offers some new readings, adopted almost integrally by Hasan Djafar (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:HasanDjafar1991_01"/><citedRange>10-11</citedRange></bibl>). This first Kebantenan plate is re-edited here by Aditia Gunawan &amp; Arlo Griffiths from photos of the plate, kindly made available to us by Terrylia Feisrami.</p>
